                "name": "Jesse Raffield",
                "href": "/profile/Jesse-Raffield-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Contrary to what you might think, it is actually pretty rare for a scientist to name something after themselves. It\u2019s seen by other scientists as self-serving and arrogant. What usually happens is that a scientist discovers something new or invents a new method, and other scientists begin to associate that discovery with the original scientist. Interestingly enough, naming something after yourself is one way to score points in the Crackpot index. ",
