            "answer_text": "They mostly don't - it is their colleagues who refer to \u201cthe method of Jones (1994)\u201d, for example. Eventually it is often just called \u201cthe Jones method\u201d. At an international scientific meeting in 1988, my colleague John Philip announced that a hypothetical soil with particular physical properties that I had proposed and investigated should be officially known as the \u201cKnight soil\u201d. The name doesn\u2019t seem to have caught on. ",
